        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "For some reason, ControllerTestCase uses __get() and a switch statement instead of distinct methods to provide access to a small handful of member variables. This is arguably an abuse of __get(), but more importantly it suppresses any PHP errors that would result from accessing an undefined attribute in a test case. Test cases should fail loudly if anything is out of place, so this behavior is counterproductive. "
        },
