        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42087",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I want to agree with Chris. I just got through a day-long debugging sessions in {{Zend_Test_PHPUnit_ControllerTestCase}} because all I got were errors similar to \"Failed asserting X is Y\".\r\n\r\nI have a smallish patch that I'm working on to fix though. Will share later today\/tomorrow.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-08-24T07:17:46.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-08-24T07:17:46.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42316",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I disregarded my patch and wrote [a custom listener for PHPUnit instead|http:\/\/github.com\/till\/Lagged_Test_PHPUnit_ControllerTestCase_Listener#readme]. \r\n\r\nI guess that's the cleaner way until someone improves this.\r\n\r\nAlso have a blog post explaining it:\r\nhttp:\/\/till.klampaeckel.de\/blog\/archives\/116-Debugging-Zend_Test.html",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-09-19T19:20:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-09-19T20:00:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47544",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "To install it, get it from PEARfarm: http:\/\/pearfarm.org\/till\/Lagged_Test_PHPUnit_ControllerTestCase_Listener",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-18T18:52:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-18T18:52:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47750",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Till -- how does your listener address the OP's problem, exactly? From what I can see, it simply listens for error conditions, and, when found, adds some output (very useful output I might add!) to the buffer. While this can help you to analyze the test conditions a bit more, it doesn't really address the idea of addressing unknown attributes. That said: care to contribute the listener to the framework? I think it could be an invaluable addition. :)\r\n\r\nChris: would raising an InvalidArgumentException (or similar) in __get() for unknown values solve the issue you're seeing for now? We can't really remove __get() or the logic it contains in the ZF1 branch, as this would be a BC break. However, introducing the exception seems an appropriate compromise.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-28T20:16:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-28T20:16:14.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
